<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900927-0019</DOCNO><DOCID>900927-0019.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- MCA Inc.:   Firm's Shares Surge $7.25   On News of Takeover Talks</HL><DATE>09/27/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   MCA MC</CO><IN>RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   Shares of MCA Inc. surged $7.25 a share to close at $61.25in New York Stock Exchange composite trading, based on aseries of rumors suggesting that MCA's talks to be acquiredby Matsushita Electric Industrial Co. were progressingrapidly.   However, MCA issued a statement after the close of tradingthat merely repeated its confirmation on Tuesday that it istalking about a friendly buy-out with a &quot;major internationalcompany&quot; which it didn't identify. MCA, based in UniversalCity, Calif., said it issued the statement after the BigBoard asked if there were any corporate developments thatwould explain the jump in MCA shares.</LP><TEXT>   People familiar with the discussions have said thatTokyo-based Matsushita could pay between $80 and $90 a sharefor MCA, or a total of $7.4 billion to $8.3 billion.   Several takeover stock traders attributed the surge in MCAshares just before the close to a panic among professionaltraders who want to own big positions in MCA if a deal isannounced soon. &quot;People are trying to make a whole year'sprofit on this one deal. They're afraid that the train isleaving the station,&quot; said one takeover-stock trader.</TEXT></DOC>